<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="488" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/449:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-29T23:00:00+02:00">March 29, 1934—11
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received March 29—7:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>18. Turkish Government consents definitely to arrest and detain
                                Insull on receiving from me certified copy of complete text of (1)
                                warrant of arrest and (2) judicial record. These must be cabled in
                                full to reach me Friday.<note n="40" xml:id="d488fn40">March
                                    30.</note> Meantime Government will endeavor to detain Insull’s
                                ship until Saturday morning, being powerless to proceed with arrest
                                until documents mentioned are in hand.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>